## Follow-up: notdiamond custom_router
Audit (reviewer asked to check for missing integrations) found notdiamond/
custom_router.py exposes two public @weave.op helpers — train_router and
evaluate_router — that call the NotDiamond client but weren't stamped (they use
the bare @weave.op decorator, not the settings.op_settings path). Added
NOTDIAMOND_INTEGRATION = library_integration("notdiamond") and attributes=
NOTDIAMOND_INTEGRATION.as_attributes() on both decorators. Left the 3 inner
_DummyEvalModel.predict ops unstamped on purpose: they're eval scaffolding over
precomputed dataframes, not notdiamond calls. ruff + ast clean; notdiamond lib
not installed locally so not runtime-tested.
